f0aa5ec027010e500bee9148be6315b9785c8fdf24ae2aa9266e8da70b4a" style=3D"text=
-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">20 months</a> in Chapter 11, to rejec=
t some money-losing contracts while keeping others. =E2=80=9CThis is an R.S=
=2EN. issue,=E2=80=9D Ross said. =E2=80=9CThi=
s is not the first R.S.N. to get=
 into these problems. But some of the market dynamics in New York allowed
this to last longer.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">MSG carries one of the highest costs of al=
l R.S.N.s in the country, Ross said, due to the fact that both Cablevision=
=E2=80=94the former vessel of Jim=E2=80=99s father <strong>Charles</strong>=
 <strong>Dolan</strong>=E2=80=99s generational wealth=E2=80=94and Verizon F=
ios competed bitterly for video subscribers in New York. =E2=80=9CThey were=
 battling for broadband subscribers, so they would never drop content, beca=
use the value of the
subscriber was too high in this broadband battle that they were having,=E2=
=80=9D Ross said. =E2=80=9CThat competitive dynamic pushed the prices up. N=
ow, the video bundle isn=E2=80=99t dragging along broadband. We=E2=80=99re =
in a totally different era.=E2=80=9D</p></div>
